    • Method Detail

      • parent

        AtRuleMember parent(AtRule atRule)
        Sets the parent AtRule. Generally this is handled automatically when this block is set on the AtRule, so it is not recommended to call this method manually.

        Do not use this method to move a block from one parent to another.

        Parameters:
        atRule - The parent at-rule.
        Returns:
        this, for chaining.
        See Also:
        AbstractAtRuleMember

      • parent

        AtRule parent()
        Gets the parent AtRule that owns this property, or absent if not set. This will not be set for dynamically created units not yet added to an AtRule instance.
        Returns:
        The parent AtRule, or an empty Optional if not present.
